Building Inclusive AI for African Languages

## Overview

This project explores the Mozilla Data Collective Hausa Speech Dataset to understand how community-driven multilingual datasets can improve artificial intelligence for underrepresented African languages.

The project aims to promote inclusive, ethical, and accessible AI by encouraging the use of open datasets for speech recognition, language preservation, and AI research across Africa.

## Objectives

- Explore the Mozilla Data Collective Hausa Speech Dataset.
- Understand the role of multilingual speech datasets in AI.
- Support inclusive AI for African languages.
- Promote responsible and ethical AI development.
- Share project findings with the open-source community.

## Dataset

- Mozilla Data Collective Hausa Speech Dataset

## Tools

- Python
- Jupyter Notebook
- GitHub

## Expected Outcomes

- Improved understanding of African language datasets.
- Practical experience working with speech AI datasets.
- Open documentation for researchers, developers, and the AI community.

## Future Work

